te \\\n  --jq '.[] | {id, path, line, author: .user.login, body: .body[:80]}'\n```\n\n### Resolving a review thread\n\nResolution requires GraphQL — there is no REST endpoint. You need the thread's GraphQL node ID (the `PRRT_...` ID from the `pr-reviews` script or from the GraphQL reviewThreads query):\n\n```bash\ngh api graphql -f query='\nmutation($threadId: ID!) {\n  resolveReviewThread(input: {threadId: $threadId}) {\n    thread { isResolved }\n  }\n}' -f threadId=\"PRRT_kwDOxxxxxx\"\n```\n\nTo unresolve:\n```bash\ngh api graphql -f query='\nmutation($threadId: ID!) {\n  unresolveReviewThread(input: {threadId: $threadId}) {\n    thread { isResolved }\n  }\n}' -f threadId=\"PRRT_kwDOxxxxxx\"\n```\n\n### Commenting on a PR (top-level, not inline review)\n\nTop-level PR comments use the issues API (PRs are issues in GitHub's model):\n\n```bash\n# Add a comment\ngh pr comment 123 -R owner/repo --body \"Thanks for the review, all addressed\"\n\n# Or with body-file for multi-line\ngh pr comment 123 -R owner/repo --body-file /tmp/comment.md\n```\n\n## Issue Relationships (Sub-issues, Parent/Child)\n\nThe `gh issue` CLI does not natively support sub-issues or parent relationships. Use `gh api` with the REST endpoints directly. These endpoints require the `2026-03-10` API version header.\n\n### Key gotcha: issue `id` vs `number`\n\nThe sub-issues API takes `sub_issue_id` which is the **internal numeric ID**, not the issue number. `gh issue view --json id` returns the GraphQL `node_id` (wrong). Get the correct integer ID with:\n\n```bash\ngh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/42 --jq '.id'\n```\n\n### Add a sub-issue (parent/child relationship)\n\nThere is no \"set parent\" API — you can only add a child to a parent. To set a parent for an issue, call `addSubIssue` on the parent with the child's ID. Both REST and GraphQL work:\n\n```bash\n# REST: add child to parent (uses internal integer ID)\nCHILD_ID=$(gh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/CHILD_NUMBER --jq '.id')\ngh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/PARENT_NUMBER/sub_issues \\\n  -X POST -F \"sub_issue_id=$CHILD_ID\"\n\n# GraphQL: add child to parent (uses node_id)\ngh api graphql -f query='\nmutation($parentId: ID!, $childId: ID!) {\n  addSubIssue(input: {issueId: $parentId, subIssueId: $childId}) {\n    issue { number title }\n    subIssue { number title }\n  }\n}' -f parentId=\"$(gh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/PARENT --jq '.node_id')\" \\\n   -f childId=\"$(gh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/CHILD --jq '.node_id')\"\n```\n\n### List sub-issues\n\n```bash\ngh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/PARENT_NUMBER/sub_issues \\\n  --jq '.[] | {number, title, state}'\n```\n\n### Get parent of an issue\n\n```bash\ngh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/CHILD_NUMBER/parent --jq '{number, title}'\n```\n\n### Remove a sub-issue\n\n```bash\nCHILD_ID=$(gh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/CHILD_NUMBER --jq '.id')\ngh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/PARENT_NUMBER/sub_issue \\\n  -X DELETE -F \"sub_issue_id=$CHILD_ID\"\n```\n\n### Blocked / blocked-by (issue dependencies)\n\nSame `id` gotcha as sub-issues — the API takes the internal integer ID, not the issue number.\n\n```bash\n# Mark issue 43 as blocked by issue 42\nBLOCKER_ID=$(gh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/42 --jq '.id')\ngh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/43/dependencies/blocked_by \\\n  -X POST -F \"issue_id=$BLOCKER_ID\"\n\n# List what's blocking issue 43\ngh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/43/dependencies/blocked_by \\\n  --jq '.[] | {number, title, state}'\n\n# List what issue 42 is blocking\ngh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/42/dependencies/blocking \\\n  --jq '.[] | {number, title, state}'\n\n# Remove the dependency\nBLOCKER_ID=$(gh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/42 --jq '.id')\ngh api repos/OWNER/REPO/issues/43/dependencies/blocked_by/$BLOCKER_ID -X DELETE\n```\n\n## Search\n\n```bash\ngh search code \"pattern\" --repo owner/repo        # search code in a repo\ngh search issues \"label:bug state:open\"            # search issues\ngh search prs \"is:open review:required\"            # search 