            "content": "# org-units — nested org-unit lifecycle\n\n## ADDED Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Nested org units with materialized ID paths\nThe system SHALL model org units (SPEC §7.2) as an arbitrarily nested tree via `parent_id`, with a materialized ID-based `path` (`rootId/childId/…`; a root's path is its own id). Renames SHALL never rewrite paths; only subtree moves SHALL.\n\n#### Scenario: Child creation materializes the ancestor path\n- **WHEN** a child unit is created under a parent with path `A/B`\n- **THEN** the child's path is `A/B/<childId>` and its `parent_id` is `B`\n\n#### Scenario: Rename leaves paths untouched\n- **WHEN** a unit is renamed\n- **THEN** its `path` and every descendant's `path` are unchanged\n\n### Requirement: Path consistency is a database invariant\nThe database SHALL reject (via constraint trigger) any `org_units` insert or update where `path` does not equal the parent's path plus `/` plus the unit's id (or the unit's own id for roots). Application code (row locks on parent/moved rows) SHALL serialize concurrent structural writes so legitimate operations do not trip the trigger.\n\n#### Scenario: Inconsistent path write is rejected\n- **WHEN** any code path attempts to write an `org_units` row whose `path` disagrees with its `parent_id`\n- **THEN** the database rejects the write with a constraint violation\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrent move and child-create stay consistent\n- **WHEN** a subtree move and a child creation under that subtree execute concurrently\n- **THEN** both either serialize to a consistent tree or one fails cleanly — no committed row may hold a stale path\n\n### Requirement: Subtree move\nThe system SHALL support moving a unit (and its whole subtree) under a new parent via `PATCH /api/v1/org-units/:id` with `parentId`. The caller MUST be owner/admin on both the source path and the destination path (RLS-enforced). A move into the unit's own subtree SHALL be rejected with 422.\n\n#### Scenario: Move rewrites every descendant path\n- **WHEN** an authorized caller moves unit `B` (path `A/B`) under `C` (path `A/C`)\n- **THEN** `B`'s path becomes `A/C/B` and every descendant's path prefix is rewritten accordingly, atomically\n\n#### Scenario: Move into own subtree is rejected\n- **WHEN** a caller attempts to move a unit under one of its own descendants (or itself)\n- **THEN** the API responds 422 and no row changes\n\n#### Scenario: Move requires rights on the destination\n- **WHEN** a caller who is admin on the source but has no owner/admin role on the destination path attempts a move\n- **THEN** the write is denied (RLS `WITH CHECK`) and surfaces as 403\n\n### Requirement: Rename\nThe system SHALL support renaming a unit via `PATCH /api/v1/org-units/:id` with `name` (1–200 chars, non-blank), restricted to owner/admin on the unit's path.\n\n#### Scenario: Admin renames a unit\n- **WHEN** an ancestor admin renames a unit\n- **THEN** the API responds 200 with the updated unit\n\n### Requirement: Leaf-only, owner-only deletion\nThe system SHALL support deleting a unit via `DELETE /api/v1/org-units/:id` only when it has no children (FK `RESTRICT`) and the caller is an owner on its path (RLS). Deleting a unit SHALL cascade its membership rows.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete with children is refused\n- **WHEN** an owner attempts to delete a unit that has child units\n- **THEN** the API responds 409 with guidance to delete or move children first\n\n#### Scenario: Non-owner cannot delete\n- **WHEN** an admin (not owner) attempts to delete a leaf unit\n- **THEN** the deletion is denied and surfaces as 403 or 404 (invisible), never a partial delete\n\n### Requirement: Visibility scoping\nOrg-unit reads SHALL be scoped by FORCE RLS: a unit is visible to users holding any membership on the unit or an ancestor, and to its creator (bootstrap edge). `GET /api/v1/org-units` SHALL return exactly the visible set, path-ordered. Requests naming an invisible unit SHALL yield 404 (anti-enumeration), not 403.\n\n#### Scenario: Stranger sees nothing\n- **WHEN** a user with no memberships in an org requests that org's unit by id\n- **THEN** the API responds 404\n\n#### Scenario: Unscoped database context fails closed\n- **WHEN** a query runs without `app.current_user_id` set\n- **THEN** RLS returns zero org-unit rows\n\n### Requirement: Root creation bootstraps ownership atomically\nCreating a root unit (`POST /api/v1/org-units`) SHALL create the unit and the creator's `owner` membership in one transaction — an org unit tree SHALL never exist without an owner.\n\n#### Scenario: Root creation grants creator ownership\n- **WHEN** an authenticated user creates a root unit\n- **THEN** the unit exists with the creator as `owner`, both from the same transaction\n",
