            "content": "# org-memberships — membership & role management\n\n## ADDED Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Explicit memberships with read-time inheritance\nThe system SHALL store one explicit membership row per (user, org unit) with a role from SPEC §7.3 (`owner, admin, maintainer, member, viewer, guest, service_account`). Inherited memberships SHALL NOT be materialized; effective roles resolve at read time along the ancestor path, nearest node winning.\n\n#### Scenario: Nearest membership wins\n- **WHEN** a user is `admin` on the root and `viewer` on a nested team\n- **THEN** their effective role on that team resolves to `viewer` (inherited=false) and on sibling teams to `admin` (inherited=true)\n\n#### Scenario: Subtree move preserves memberships\n- **WHEN** a subtree is moved to a new parent\n- **THEN** no membership rows change; effective roles re-resolve along the new path\n\n### Requirement: Grant\nOwners/admins on a unit's ancestor path SHALL be able to grant memberships (`POST /api/v1/org-units/:id/memberships`) with role limited by DTO to `{admin, member, maintainer, viewer, guest}` — never `owner` or `service_account`. Duplicate grants SHALL yield 409 (no silent role change).\n\n#### Scenario: Non-admin cannot grant\n- **WHEN** a plain `member` attempts to grant a membership\n- **THEN** RLS denies the insert and the API responds 403\n\n#### Scenario: Cross-tenant grant is denied\n- **WHEN** an admin of org A attempts to grant a membership on a unit in org B\n- **THEN** RLS denies the insert and the API responds 403\n\n#### Scenario: Duplicate grant conflicts\n- **WHEN** a caller grants a role to an existing member of the unit\n- **THEN** the API responds 409\n\n### Requirement: Owner cannot be minted outside bootstrap and transfer\nThe datastore SHALL enforce (RLS `WITH CHECK`) that `role = 'owner'` rows are writable only by (a) the creator-bootstrap branch on a fresh root, and (b) the ownership-transfer function. No API surface, and no direct-SQL path under a user context, SHALL create or set `owner` otherwise.\n\n#### Scenario: Ancestor admin cannot mint owner via general grant\n- **WHEN** an ancestor owner/admin inserts a membership with `role = 'owner'` through the general grant path\n- **THEN** the database rejects the write\n\n### Requirement: Roster visibility for admin tier\nOwners/admins on a unit or its ancestors SHALL see the unit's membership rows (recursion-safe `SECURITY DEFINER` visibility arm). All other users SHALL see only their own membership rows. `GET /api/v1/org-units/:id/memberships` SHALL return the roster to authorized callers and 404 when the unit is invisible.\n\n#### Scenario: Ancestor admin lists the roster\n- **WHEN** an admin on the root requests a descendant unit's roster\n- **THEN** all membership rows of that unit are returned\n\n#### Scenario: Plain member sees only self\n- **WHEN** a `member` queries memberships\n- **THEN** only their own rows are visible; the roster endpoint responds 403\n\n#### Scenario: Roster is cross-tenant invisible\n- **WHEN** an admin of org A requests the roster of a unit in org B\n- **THEN** the API responds 404 and zero rows are readable\n\n### Requirement: Owner rows are immutable through general admin paths\nAdmin-arm UPDATE and DELETE policies SHALL exclude rows with `role = 'owner'`: widening roster visibility SHALL NOT enable an admin to demote or revoke an owner. This guard SHALL land in the same migration as the visibility widening.\n\n#### Scenario: Admin cannot demote an owner\n- **WHEN** an ancestor admin attempts to update an `owner` membership row to any other role\n- **THEN** zero rows are affected and the API surfaces 403 or 404\n\n#### Scenario: Admin cannot revoke an owner\n- **WHEN** an ancestor admin attempts to delete an `owner` membership row\n- **THEN** zero rows are affected\n\n### Requirement: Role update\nOwners/admins SHALL be able to change a member's role via `PATCH /api/v1/org-units/:id/memberships/:userId` with role limited by DTO to `{admin, maintainer, member, viewer, guest}`. Setting `owner` SHALL be impossible through this surface (DTO and RLS `WITH CHECK`).\n\n#### Scenario: Admin changes a member's role\n- **WHEN** an ancestor admin updates a `member` to `viewer`\n- **THEN** the row's role changes and the API responds 200/204\n\n### Requirement: Revoke and self-leave\nOwners/admins SHALL be able to revoke a non-owner membership (`DELETE /api/v1/org-units/:id/memberships/:userId`); any user SHALL be able to remove their own membership (leave), subject to the last-owner invariant.\n\n#### Scenario: Admin removes a member\n- **WHEN** an ancestor admin deletes another user's non-owner membership\n- **THEN** the row is deleted and the API responds 204\n\n#### Scenario: Member leaves a unit\n- **WHEN** a user deletes their own membership\n- **THEN** the row is deleted and the API responds 204\n\n### Requirement: Last-owner invariant\nThe database SHALL reject (constraint trigger) any update or delete that would leave a unit that has owner memberships with zero of them. The API SHALL surface this as 409 with guidance to transfer ownership first.\n\n#### Scenario: Sole owner cannot leave\n- **WHEN** the only owner of a root org deletes their own membership\n- **THEN** the database rejects the delete and the API responds 409 with a transfer-ownership hint\n\n### Requirement: Ownership transfer\nAn explicit owner of a unit SHALL be able to transfer ownership via `POST /api/v1/org-units/:id/ownership-transfers` to an existing explicit member of that unit. The transfer SHALL be atomic: the target becomes `owner` and the caller is demoted to `admin` in one operation. This is the only owner-minting path after bootstrap.\n\n#### Scenario: Owner transfers to a member\n- **WHEN** the owner transfers ownership to an existing member of the unit\n- **THEN** the target's role is `owner`, the caller's role is `admin`, atomically\n\n#### Scenario: Non-owner cannot transfer\n- **WHEN** an admin (not owner) invokes ownership transfer\n- **THEN** the API responds 403 and no roles change\n\n#### Scenario: Transfer to a non-member is refused\n- **WHEN** the owner names a user with no explicit membership on the unit\n- **THEN** the API responds 404 and no roles change\n\n### Requirement: Effective-role lookup\nThe system SHALL expose the caller's effective role on a unit (explicit or inherited, nearest-wins) for downstream consumers (policy engine #45, config resolver #46, and the web UI's permission-aware rendering).\n\n#### Scenario: No membership on the path\n- **WHEN** a user with no membership anywhere on a unit's path resolves their role\n- **THEN** the result is null (and the unit itself is invisible to them unless they created it)\n",
