            "content": "# org-admin-ui — web UX for organization management\n\n## ADDED Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Organization settings area\nThe web app SHALL provide an organization-management area under settings, listing the caller's visible org units as a tree (assembled client-side from the path-ordered flat list), with actions to create a root org and create child units. All rendering SHALL compose `@workspace/ui` primitives and DESIGN.md semantic tokens.\n\n#### Scenario: First-run empty state\n- **WHEN** a user with no org units opens the organizations settings page\n- **THEN** an empty state invites them to create their first organization/household\n\n#### Scenario: Tree reflects nesting\n- **WHEN** a user belongs to an org with nested teams\n- **THEN** the tree renders parents before children with visible depth\n\n### Requirement: Unit management page\nEach unit SHALL have a management view with: inline rename, move (parent picker that excludes the unit's own subtree), member roster, and a danger zone (delete leaf unit, transfer ownership) — each destructive action behind a confirmation dialog that names the object and consequence.\n\n#### Scenario: Move picker blocks own subtree\n- **WHEN** the user opens the move-parent picker for a unit\n- **THEN** the unit itself and its descendants are not selectable (server remains authoritative)\n\n#### Scenario: Destructive confirmation names the object\n- **WHEN** the user initiates unit deletion or member removal\n- **THEN** the confirmation dialog states exactly what will happen to what (e.g. \"Remove Alice from Platform?\")\n\n### Requirement: Roster and role controls\nThe roster SHALL show each member with a role badge; owners/admins SHALL be able to change roles (excluding `owner`) and remove members from the roster view; every user SHALL have a leave action on their own row. Controls the caller lacks rights for SHALL not render — while the API remains the actual gate.\n\n#### Scenario: Admin edits roles from the roster\n- **WHEN** an admin changes a member's role in the roster\n- **THEN** the mutation calls the API and the roster refreshes on success\n\n#### Scenario: Viewer sees no management controls\n- **WHEN** a `viewer` opens a unit they can see\n- **THEN** role selects, remove and danger-zone controls are absent\n\n### Requirement: Guided failure surfaces\nAPI failures SHALL surface as actionable UI, not raw errors: the last-owner 409 SHALL render an inline explanation with a transfer-ownership call-to-action; delete-with-children 409 SHALL explain that children must be moved or deleted first; 403/404 render permission-safe messages.\n\n#### Scenario: Sole owner tries to leave\n- **WHEN** the only owner clicks leave and the API responds 409\n- **THEN** the UI explains they are the last owner and offers the transfer-ownership flow\n\n### Requirement: Server state via TanStack Query\nOrg and roster data SHALL be fetched and mutated via TanStack Query against the API endpoints (`apps/web` stays a thin client per SPEC §22.0); mutations SHALL invalidate the affected org/roster queries.\n\n#### Scenario: Mutation refreshes dependent views\n- **WHEN** any org/membership mutation succeeds\n- **THEN** the org tree and affected roster re-fetch and re-render without a manual reload\n",
