            "command": "cat > /tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-llame/49e712ca-1f1c-4bc2-bca4-6d7a7437561a/scratchpad/issue-instance-admin.md << 'EOF'\n## Summary\n\nThe **instance scope has no owner**. SPEC §6.1 puts `Instance` above root orgs and §6.2 defines a `global` scope, but §7.3 roles are all org-scoped — nothing models who governs the instance itself. Bootstrap the first instance admin and give them registration + root-creation policy.\n\n## Context\n\n- `POST /auth/register` is open (rate-limited only, #68). Acceptable on a LAN household box; wrong for anything internet-reachable — no one can close registration, require approval, or deactivate a user.\n- Any registered user can create unlimited root orgs (creator-bootstrap, #44). Combined with open registration this is a spam/abuse vector on an exposed instance.\n- FORCE RLS means nobody — including the deployer — can see or clean up foreign orgs except via raw SQL. There is deliberately no super-context.\n- #45 (policy engine) and #46 (config resolver) will need a `global`-scope principal; without this, they'd have to invent one mid-flight.\n\nReference pattern (open-webui, the dominant self-hosted comp): **first registered user becomes instance admin; subsequent signups are pending/approved per policy.**\n\n## Design sketch\n\n- Instance-admin flag/role on `users`, granted **transactionally to the first registered user** (race-safe: unique partial index or serialized check).\n- Instance settings (initially): `registration_mode` (`open | approval | closed`), `root_org_creation` (`anyone | instance_admin`). Defaults preserve today's behavior (open / anyone) so household deployments are unaffected.\n- Registration approval flow when `registration_mode = approval` (pending users can't log in; instance admin approves/deactivates).\n- Instance-admin org visibility for cleanup is a **deliberate, audited read path** (e.g. dedicated service context like `runAsPublic`), not an RLS bypass sprinkled into policies. Scope it read+delete-abandoned only; decide the exact shape in the design doc.\n\n## Sequencing\n\nBefore the instance is ever exposed publicly, and **before #45** (gives the policy engine its `global` principal). Candidate for #52 Layer 1.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] First registration atomically creates the instance admin; concurrent first-registrations cannot mint two.\n- [ ] `registration_mode` enforced at `/auth/register`; approval flow works end-to-end.\n- [ ] `root_org_creation` enforced (RLS or service-layer, fail closed) with defaults matching current behavior.\n- [ ] Instance admin can list users and deactivate accounts; negative tests prove non-admins cannot.\n- [ ] Cross-tenant negative tests for any new visibility path.\nEOF\ngh issue create -R leon0399/llame --title \"feat(api): instance-admin bootstrap & registration policy\" --label identity --body-file /tmp/claude-1000/-home-leon0399-Projects-llame/49e712ca-1f1c-4bc2-bca4-6d7a7437561a/scratchpad/issue-instance-admin.md",
